Why Lash Extension Aftercare Matters and How to Do It Right


Eyelash extensions are the ultimate beauty investment, giving you stunning, effortless lashes every day. But to keep them looking flawless, proper aftercare is essential. Not only does it prolong the life of your extensions, but it also keeps your natural lashes healthy, prevents infections, and saves you time and money on infills. Learn top tips for lash extension aftercare from our experts:


 

The Glow Bar’s Lash Extension Aftercare Tips


The First 24-48 Hours


  • Avoid water, steam, or sweat to let the adhesive fully set.

  • Steer clear of saunas, hot showers, or rubbing your lashes during this critical period.

Daily Maintenance


  • Clean Gently: Use a lash-safe, oil-free cleanser and a soft brush to clean your lashes daily. This prevents dirt, oils, and bacteria from building up.

  • Brush Daily: Keep your lashes neat by gently combing through them with a spoolie brush.

  • Avoid Oil-Based Products: Skincare and makeup products with oils can weaken the adhesive bond.

Lifestyle Adjustments


  • Sleep on your back or with a satin pillowcase to minimise friction.

  • Avoid eyelash curlers and excessive heat exposure near your face.

  • Schedule regular infills every 2–3 weeks to maintain your lash’s fullness.

Recommended Products for Lash Aftercare


  • Foaming Lash Cleanser: Perfect for keeping lashes clean and fresh.

  • Oil-Free Makeup Remover: Ensures the adhesive stays intact.

  • Lash Serum: Strengthens and nourishes natural lashes for long-term health.


 

Let’s Keep Your Lashes Flawless
